    <item>
      <title>Noble Sword</title>
      <author>Chalmoro Azohen</author>
      <link>https://gamebanana.com/mods/583277</link>
      <comments>https://gamebanana.com/mods/583277#PostsListModule</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="false">88f746cc2e5dc7dfcd12229f466f1dfc314785ab</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 23 Mar 2025 06:19:48 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67dfa70cd5c64.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67dfa7c66e17b.jpg"/&gt;&lt;img src="https://images.gamebanana.com/img/ss/mods/67dfa7e5bd9c8.jpg"/&gt;&lt;br&gt;I've always been fascinated by the Noble Sword from the Oracle games - specifically, the version of it seen in a pedestal in &lt;i&gt;Oracle of Seasons&lt;/i&gt;. So I made a model, cobbled together from various other things, and it resulted in something I believe is a good approximation of it. Due to the lacking graphics on the Game Boy, I had to make guesses about the proper coloration, so it isn't the sprite's red-and-yellow; I figured a bronze-ish hilt with a pale blade (a reference to the Japanese, where it's called the White Sword) would be best. Its shape is modeled somewhat after a saber, which my consultants decided was probably what the Noble Sword is supposed to be.&lt;br&gt;It'll respawn with the Blood Moon.&lt;br&gt; &lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;u&gt;Stats:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br&gt;Damage: 28&lt;br&gt;Durability: 31&lt;br&gt;Location: Coliseum</description>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/noblesword.bnp" type="application/octet-stream"/>
      <media:content url="https://files.gamebanana.com/mods/noblesword.zip" type="application/zip"/>
      <category>Swords</category>
      <category>Skins</category>
    </item>
